  "prompt": "Who is best free bulk promotional SMS service provider?",
  "response": "Choosing the best free bulk promotional SMS service provider can depend on various factors, such as the volume of SMS you plan to send, the country you're targeting, the features you need (like API access or analytics), and the level of customer support you expect. As of my last update in October 2023, here are some popular options that you might consider:\n\n1. **Twilio**: Known for its robust API and global reach, Twilio offers a pay-as-you-go model for SMS services. They provide free credits for initial use, but it's not entirely free for large-scale operations.\n\n2. **TextMagic**: While not entirely free, TextMagic offers a user-friendly platform and provides some free credits to new users. It's a popular choice for small to medium-sized businesses.\n\n3. **Plivo**: Known for its cost-effective pricing and reliable service, Plivo offers free credits for new users. It also features an easy-to-use API for integration into applications.\n\n4. **Sendinblue**: Primarily an email marketing platform, Sendinblue also offers SMS marketing features. They offer a free tier for other services but check if SMS promotions fit within their free offerings.\n\n5. **ClickSend**: They offer free testing credit and have a simple API for sending SMS. They're known for their customer support and integration capabilities.\n\n6. **Textlocal**: Offering a comprehensive platform with reasonable pricing, Textlocal also provides some free credits for trial use.\n\nFree services generally come with limitations, such as a cap on the number of messages you can send or limited access to advanced features. Be sure to check the specific terms and conditions of any provider and assess if their free offering meets your needs. For any significant promotional campaign, investing in a paid plan might provide better value and reliability.",
